HEADWORD: Fiorite
<hw>Fi"o*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
variety of opal occuring in the cavities of volcanic tufa, in smooth and
shining globular and botryoidal masses, having a pearly luster; -- so
called from <ets>Fiora</ets>, in Ischia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

